CLI query application for Jobmine (http://www.jobmine.uwaterloo.ca/) application lists.
Mailing script to send updates on your applications on jobmine. 

Add the script to CRON to send you emails. 
Useful tutorial on CRON for *nix: 
http://www.cyberciti.biz/faq/how-do-i-add-jobs-to-cron-under-linux-or-unix-oses/

If you want to run/send emails everyday from 9am to 8PM every 20 minutes:

20,40,59 9-20 * * * ~/climine/climail 

		      ^ THIS IS WHERE THE SCRIPT IS LOCATION

If you get permission errors for the CRON job, you need to use chmod

chmod a+x ~/climine/climail

If you don't want to get emails from CRON daemon append the job with
> /dev/null 2>&1
